### FruitGuard SMS API Testing Requests
@message_id = 1;
### Health Check
GET http://localhost:5000/health


### Send SMS
POST http://localhost:5000/sms/send
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "phone_numbers": ["+254742252910"],
    "message": "Alert: FruitGuard detected potential threat in your orchard!",
    "sender_id": "FruitGuard",
    "max_retries": 3
}

### Send SMS with Schedule
POST http://localhost:5000/sms/send
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "phone_numbers": ["1234567890"],
    "message": "Scheduled alert: Daily orchard status report",
    "sender_id": "FruitGuard",
    "schedule_time": "2024-01-15T08:00:00Z"
}

### Get SMS Status
GET http://localhost:5000/sms/status/{{message_id}}

### Get Account Balance
GET http://localhost:5000/account/balance

### Validate Phone Numbers
POST http://localhost:5000/sms/validate
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "phone_numbers": ["1234567890", "invalid", "+1234567890", "555-123-4567"]
}

### Delivery Report Webhook (for testing)
POST http://localhost:5000/dr
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "message_id": "test_message_123",
    "status": "delivered",
    "to": "+1234567890",
    "timestamp": "2024-01-15T10:30:00Z"
}

### Error Cases

### Missing Required Fields
POST http://localhost:5000/sms/send
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "phone_numbers": ["1234567890"]
}

### Invalid Phone Numbers
POST http://localhost:5000/sms/send
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "phone_numbers": ["invalid", "abc"],
    "message": "Test message"
}

### Empty Message
POST http://localhost:5000/sms/send
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "phone_numbers": ["1234567890"],
    "message": ""
}

